      <p>
        In no event shall APBN or its suppliers be liable for any damages (including, without limitation, damages for loss of data or profit, or due to business interruption) arising out of the use or inability to use the materials on APBN's website, even if APBN or an APBN authorized representative has been notified orally or in writing of the possibility of such damage.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="flex flex-col gap-2">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold">Links</h2>
      <p>
        APBN has not reviewed all of the sites linked to its website and is not responsible for the contents of any such linked site. The inclusion of any link does not imply endorsement by APBN. Use of any such linked website is at the user's own risk.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="flex flex-col gap-2">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold">Governing Law</h2>
      <p class="flex items-baseline gap-1">
        Any claim relating to APBN's website shall be governed by the laws of Nigeria without regard to its conflict of law provisions.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="flex flex-col gap-2">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold">Changes</h2>
      <p class="flex items-baseline gap-1">
        APBN reserves the right to modify or replace these Terms of Use at any time. It is your responsibility to check these Terms of Use periodically for changes. Your continued use of the website after any such modifications shall constitute your consent to such changes.
      </p>
    </div>
    <p>By using APBN's website, you signify your acceptance of these terms. If you do not agree to these terms, please do not use our website.</p>
  </section>
</Layout>
